@startuml sequence_store_and_forward
title n-stream-replay — Sequência: ingestão (fan-out) e store-and-forward

skinparam shadowing false
actor "Kafka origem" as src
participant "SourceConsumer\n(thread/origem)" as sc
participant "DurableSinkQueue\n(destino A)" as qa
participant "DurableSinkQueue\n(destino B)" as qb
participant "SinkForwarder A" as fa
participant "SinkForwarder B" as fb
participant "Kafka destino A" as ka
participant "Kafka destino B\n(offline)" as kb

== Ingestão (at-least-once, sync-on-commit) ==
src -> sc : poll() -> lote
loop cada record
  sc -> qa : offer(ReplayRecord)
  sc -> qb : offer(ReplayRecord)
end
sc -> qa : sync() (fsync)
sc -> qb : sync() (fsync)
sc -> src : commitSync()  (só após durar em TODAS as filas)

== Entrega independente por destino ==
fa -> qa : peekBatch() (move backlog->retry)
fa -> ka : publish(lote)
ka --> fa : ok
fa -> qa : ack() (remove prefixo entregue)

note over fb, kb
  Destino B offline: publish falha (none()).
  Itens permanecem na retry; backoff e retry.
  A origem e o destino A não são afetados.
end note
fb -> qb : peekBatch()
fb -> kb : publish(lote)
kb --> fb : timeout / connection refused
fb -> fb : backoff (mantém na fila)

== Destino B volta ==
fb -> qb : peekBatch() (mesmos itens reservados)
fb -> kb : publish(lote)
kb --> fb : ok
fb -> qb : ack()
@enduml
